==English==

===Etymology===
[[fail]] + [[over]]

===Noun===
'''failover'''
# A strategy for ensuring [[high availability]] of some [[critical]] [[resource]] (such as a [[computer]] system), involving a [[redundant]], [[backup]] system which is kept running at all times so that, upon detected [[failure]] of the [[primary]] system, processing can be [[automatically]] shifted [[over]] to the backup.
#: ''Do we have a failover strategy for the database server?''

